Bundled Go module dependencies
------------------------------

Release binaries (the goreleaser-produced archives + the Docker images) are
statically linked and include the third-party Go modules listed in `go.mod`,
under their respective licenses (MIT, BSD-2-Clause, BSD-3-Clause, Apache-2.0,
ISC, MPL-2.0). Each release archive ships:

  - `licenses/<import-path>/LICEN[SC]E*`   full license text per module
                                           (covers LICENSE, LICENCE,
                                           LICENSE.md, NOTICE, COPYING)
  - `<release-archive>.spdx.json`          SPDX-JSON Software Bill of Materials

To regenerate the per-module LICENSE bundle locally, run `make licenses`
(this is the bundle the release pipeline ships in `licenses/`). The SBOM
is produced by syft during the release pipeline; install syft locally and
run `syft .` to reproduce it ad-hoc.
